revision.text:
A post-hoc analysis is a statistical test carried out following an analysis of variance which ruled out the null hypothesis of absence of difference between group which allows identifying which groups differ. Une analyse post-hoc est un test statistique effectué à la suite d'une analyse de variance qui exclut l'hypothèse nulle d'absence de différence entre les groupes permettant d'identifier les groupes qui diffèrent. Alejandra Gonzalez-Beltran Jean-Marc Meunier Orlaith Burke Philippe Rocca-Serra a posteriori test adapted from wikipedia: http://en.wikip
is a subclass from http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/STATO_0000279
